dct_title_s: A general plott and description of the Fennes: and surrounded grounds in the sixe counties of Norfolke, Suffolke, Cambridge, with in the Isle of Ely, Huntington, Northampton and Lincolne etc.; Amstelodami, sumptibus Henrici Hondii.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Map is oriented with North to the right. In lower right corner, a box of text titled "Illustrissimis, magnificis, et generosis dominis, dominis" and surrounded with farming equipment and fruits. In the lower left corner, the scale is also surrounded by farming implements. There are ships in the sea and a coat of arms in the upper right corner. The map bears the date 1632. This state was published in atlases by Jan Jansson and Henricus Hondius in 1633 and 1637. From the Appendix Atlas of the British Isles and Northern Europe, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan. 1 map; 45 x 56 cm.
dct_creator_sm: Hondius, Hendrik, 1597-1651. Appendix Atlas of the British Isles and Northern Europe
